# CC PROMPT — v2.33.19 — feat(tools): log_timeline — unified cross-source timeline per entity

## What this does

Adds a single MCP tool that returns a chronologically merged timeline for an
entity, drawing from four sources that the agent currently has to query
separately and correlate by hand:

1. `operation_log` — agent tool calls scoped to this entity
2. `agent_actions` (v2.31.2) — destructive actions audit
3. `entity_history` (v2.9.0) — status transitions, config hash changes (drift v2.33.9)
4. Elasticsearch logs — filtered to entity's host/service within window

Observed cost: most investigate traces spend ~40% of their tool budget
reconstructing this timeline. This single call replaces 4-5 other calls and
gives the agent a clean synthesis input.

Version bump: 2.33.18 → 2.33.19

